14 WHEREAS, Code Section 20-2-771 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated authorizes
15 and requires the Department of Education to collaborate with public health authorities to
16 address health related mandates for students; and
17 WHEREAS, effective screening programs can identify vision and hearing impairments early,
18 allowing timely interventions that support academic success and literacy development.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GEORGIA GENERAL ASSEMBLY
20 that:
21 (1) The Department of Education and Department of Public Health are urged to
22 collaborate in developing a comprehensive strategy and methods to expand vision and
23 hearing screening for students in pre-kindergarten, kindergarten, and first, third, fifth, and
24 eighth grades, as well as for transfer students in all grade levels; and
25 (2) Such comprehensive strategy and methods, once developed, shall be presented to the
26 chairpersons of the House Committee on Education and the Senate Education and Youth
27 Committee and the Georgia Council on Literacy to ensure alignment with state literacy
28 goals.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
31 representatives of the Department of Education and the Department of Public Health.
